 {"id":"franken_numpy-y197","title":"fnp-python frompyfunc blindly delegates reduce to upstream numpy","description":"The working tree changes to fnp-python/src/lib.rs unconditionally import numpy in PyFromPyFunc::new_checked and delegate the reduce method directly to NumPy's ufunc via numpy_ufunc.bind(py).call_method(\"reduce\", ...). This completely bypasses franken_numpy's ufunc reduction engine, offloads execution back to upstream NumPy, and introduces a hard runtime dependency on NumPy. It defeats the purpose of the parity bead franken_numpy-gc7y. fnp-ufunc should implement identity and reduce directly for Python callables instead of delegating to NumPy.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T17:05:23.454873943Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T17:49:27.299250248Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T17:49:27.297345697Z","close_reason":"Implemented local frompyfunc reduce parity without NumPy delegation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
